data.name: label11.Text
data.value:
Most Drag&&Drop implementations in WinForms using preview images struggle with controls that have AllowDrop set to false or don't implement GetFeedback. This causes the preview to stutter, freeze or even to disappear while the mouse is moved.
Fluent Drag&&Drop uses a mouse hook that allows the preview images to be moved over each kind of control or app without getting laggy. Even without the mouse hook, Fluent Drag&&Drop should be smoother than alternative implementations.

data.name: label15.Text
data.value: The compatibility does not stop with standard WinForms controls but supports Drag&&Drop operations with other applications as well, like the Windows Explorer or any modern web browser. Try it out ...

data.name: label14.Text
data.value: Fluent Drag&&Drop provides an easier and richer experience but uses the same API to implement Drag&&Drop operations as every standard WinForms control. This makes Fluent Drag&&Drop compatible with existing implementations.

data.name: label13.Text
data.value:
FluentDragDrop provides three extension points to add effects: - Start - Drop (after a successful drag && drop operation) - Cancel (after an unsuccessful drag && drop operation)
This sample is using prebuilt effects from the NuGet package "FluentDragDrop.Effects": - Start: FadeIn - Drop: a composite effect of the prebuilt FadeOut effect and a custom color flash of the target control - Cancel: Return to source control
